The paper discusses the design of scoring mechanisms, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The focus on responsible design also suggests a potential fit for the cybersecurity (cs.CR) and cyber ethics (cs.CY) sub-categories. Finally, the use of function sampling and perturbation techniques may also relate to the field of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
